<subSubSection id="21C4BAC2C62F1B1AFF6CFFBEFCA1FE71" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6961E949C62F1B1AFF6CFFBEFCA1FE71" blockId="41.[151,1436,151,428]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC62F1B1AFF6CFFBEFEBEFF6D" bold="true" box="[199,315,152,176]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="0D4F94B8C62F1B1AFEEAFFB1FDEDFF72" author="Apel, M. &amp; Spiridonov, V." box="[321,616,151,175]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="159 - 331" refId="ref45102" refString="Apel, M. &amp; Spiridonov, V. (1998) Taxonomic and zoogeography of the Portunid crabs (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Portunidae) of the Persian Gulf and adjacent waters. Fauna of Arabia, 17, 159 - 331." type="journal article" year="1998">Apel &amp; Spiridonov (1998)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned some variations in the shape of the frontal lobes, anterolateral teeth of the carapace and pilosity of the carapace. A small male (CL = 9.23, CB = 13.28 mm) collected during the study from the south coast of the 
<collectingCountry id="11C9A9D9C62F1B1AFDA4FFF9FDDBFF2A" box="[527,606,223,247]" name="Iran" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Qeshm</collectingCountry>
I. has a relatively plumose carapace, and the first three anterolateral teeth of the carapace are nearly blunt, whereas specimens examined by 
<bibRefCitation id="0D4F94B8C62F1B1AFCD1FE22FB24FEC1" author="Apel, M. &amp; Spiridonov, V." box="[890,1185,260,284]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="159 - 331" refId="ref45102" refString="Apel, M. &amp; Spiridonov, V. (1998) Taxonomic and zoogeography of the Portunid crabs (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Portunidae) of the Persian Gulf and adjacent waters. Fauna of Arabia, 17, 159 - 331." type="journal article" year="1998">Apel &amp; Spiridonov (1998)</bibRefCitation>
from the Persian Gulf have acute teeth. The Persian Gulf population of this species has usually the frontal lobe laterally produced (
<bibRefCitation id="0D4F94B8C62F1B1AFACFFE01FEFEFEB9" author="Apel, M. &amp; Spiridonov, V." pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="159 - 331" refId="ref45102" refString="Apel, M. &amp; Spiridonov, V. (1998) Taxonomic and zoogeography of the Portunid crabs (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Portunidae) of the Persian Gulf and adjacent waters. Fauna of Arabia, 17, 159 - 331." type="journal article" year="1998">Apel &amp; Spiridonov 1998</bibRefCitation>
), while in the present specimen it is indistinct. 
<bibRefCitation id="0D4F94B8C62F1B1AFC1EFE6AFB6EFEB9" author="Apel, M. &amp; Spiridonov, V." box="[949,1259,332,356]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="159 - 331" refId="ref45102" refString="Apel, M. &amp; Spiridonov, V. (1998) Taxonomic and zoogeography of the Portunid crabs (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Portunidae) of the Persian Gulf and adjacent waters. Fauna of Arabia, 17, 159 - 331." type="journal article" year="1998">Apel &amp; Spiridonov (1998)</bibRefCitation>
stated that the occurrence of this species in the eastern Indian Ocean is doubtful, since some records from the region (
<bibRefCitation id="0D4F94B8C62F1B1AFABEFE49FA12FE5A" author="Sakai, T." box="[1301,1431,367,391]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="365 - 741" refId="ref52176" refString="Sakai, T. (1939) Studies on the crabs of Japan. IV. Brachygnatha, Brachyrhyncha. Science Reports of the Tokyo Bunrika Daigaku, (B) 3 (Supplement 3), 365 - 741, pls. 42 - 111." type="journal article" year="1939">Sakai 1939</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="0D4F94B8C62F1B1AFF3CFEB2FE37FE71" author="Stephenson, W. &amp; Rees, M." box="[151,434,404,428]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="1 - 114" refId="ref53008" refString="Stephenson, W. &amp; Rees, M. (1967) Some portunid crabs from the Pacific and Indian Oceans in the collections of the Smithsonian Institution. Proceedings of the U. S. National Museum, 120 (3556), 1 - 114." type="journal article" year="1967">Stephenson &amp; Rees 1967</bibRefCitation>
) are based on misidentifications.
</paragraph>
